===Etymology===
According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, this is a Southeast Asian etymon. Compare {{cog|poz-pro|*te(m)biŋ||border, edge, shore, bank}} & {{cog|mkh-mnc-pro|*t(r)mɓaɲ||rim, edge; lips}}.

Unclear, if possible, connection with Tibeto-Burman lexical items: {{cog|lep|ᰓᰧᰶ|tr=bí|t=edge, border}} & {{m|lep|ᰜᰤᰴ ᰓᰧᰶ|tr=lyaŋ bí|t=utmost limit of a place}}; {{cog|bo|ཕྱི}} ~ {{m|bo|ཕྱིན|t=outside}} (unless the Tibetan items belong to {{och-l|比|behind > outside?|id=1}}) (ibid.).

{{och-l|瀕}} is possibly its [[endopassive]] derivative. {{och-l|墳|tr=-}} ~ {{och-l|濆}} is possibly its vocalic variant (ibid.).

